# mklinks Configuration File Example (Windows)
# 
# Line 1: Destination directory (where symlinks will be created)
# Lines 2+: Directory names to exclude (one per line)
# 
# Empty lines and lines starting with # are ignored
#
# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file and name it mklinks.conf (or any name)
# 2. Edit Line 1 to your destination directory path
# 3. Add any directories you want to exclude (optional)
# 4. Run: .\mklinks.ps1 mklinks.conf

